1
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:12,233
<i> Stop the car now!</i>

2
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:17,300
<i> Sir Tonyo.</i>

3
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:18,667
<i>How about Reign?
Did you see her inside?</i>

4
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:21,400
<i>We can't risk getting
all of us caught.</i>

5
00:00:21,533 --> 00:00:23,633
<i>Let's take Selena
to the safehouse first.</i>

6
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:26,200
<i>And from there, we'll plan how
to save your godsister.</i>

7
00:00:26,333 --> 00:00:27,133
<i> Sir!</i>

8
00:00:27,267 --> 00:00:29,067
<i>We'd like to ask for help, Sir.</i>

9
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:32,833
<i>Our friend didn't make it
to our meeting place.</i>

10
00:00:32,967 --> 00:00:35,233
<i>Couldn't this be connected
to the human trafficking</i>

11
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:36,467
<i> that Conde is investigating?</i>

12
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:38,400
<i>Bok, it seems like you don't
want to call Chief?</i>

13
00:00:38,533 --> 00:00:41,333
<i>Because if he finds out
that we've got Selena,</i>

14
00:00:41,467 --> 00:00:42,600
<i> he'll definitely send us home.</i>

15
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:45,667
<i>Even if we haven't saved
Enriquez's godsister yet?</i>

16
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:47,000
<i>I need to go back to get Reign.</i>

17
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:50,467
<i>Bobby, we'll go back tomorrow.
We'll save your godsister.</i>

18
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:52,133
<i>This is what I'm preparing
for...</i>

19
00:00:52,267 --> 00:00:54,633
<i>to use my fighting skills
abroad.</i>

20
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:56,067
<i>Maybe it's better
if we split up...</i>

21
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:58,367
<i>You've already thought
of what I'm thinking.</i>

22
00:00:58,500 --> 00:00:59,433
<i> Markus!</i>

23
00:01:03,933 --> 00:01:04,800
<i> Enriquez!</i>

24
00:01:04,933 --> 00:01:05,633
<i> Are you okay?</i>

25
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:06,867
<i>Chase him! That's where he went,
quick!</i>

26
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:19,700
Good day!

27
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:52,900
- Enriquez! Bok!
- Come on!

28
00:01:53,033 --> 00:01:55,200
- I told you to call me if...
- There, there, there!

29
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:30,967
What now, Sir Fred?

30
00:02:31,100 --> 00:02:34,233
We've already asked almost
everyone in the entire village.

31
00:02:34,367 --> 00:02:37,033
Nobody caught her
on anyone's CCTV.

32
00:02:37,167 --> 00:02:38,333
The hard part is,

33
00:02:38,467 --> 00:02:40,833
we don't know if Cherry was
riding a motorcycle or a car.

34
00:02:40,967 --> 00:02:44,433
But I still have a lot of trust
in all of you.

35
00:02:44,567 --> 00:02:46,333
Especially you, Sir Fred.

36
00:02:46,467 --> 00:02:48,200
I know that you're a great
police officer.

37
00:02:51,433 --> 00:02:52,133
Really?

38
00:02:52,267 --> 00:02:53,133
Yes!

39
00:02:53,267 --> 00:02:54,233
Weren't you the one
who solved the case

40
00:02:54,367 --> 00:02:57,067
of Peach's and my missing
underwear.

41
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:00,067
Are you single, Sir Fred?

42
00:03:05,067 --> 00:03:06,433
Yes, I'm single.

43
00:03:06,567 --> 00:03:07,400
Come on.

44
00:03:07,533 --> 00:03:08,967
Let's go find your friend.

45
00:03:10,933 --> 00:03:12,533
That will not work on Sir Fred.

46
00:03:12,667 --> 00:03:16,667
It's okay, I'm not giving up
just like that.

47
00:03:18,167 --> 00:03:21,133
Mister, have you seen her?

48
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:22,467
No.

49
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,933
Okay, Mister, thank you.

50
00:03:26,467 --> 00:03:28,767
Where did that girl go?

51
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:30,233
What do you think, Sir?

52
00:03:31,433 --> 00:03:33,800
Do you have a boyfriend, Peach?

53
00:03:33,933 --> 00:03:34,867
I don't have a boyfriend.

54
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:35,667
Why?

55
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,200
Just asking.

56
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:40,500
But are you willing
to date someone if ever?

57
00:03:40,633 --> 00:03:42,033
Why not, right?

58
00:03:42,167 --> 00:03:45,733
It's hard to find a decent guy
these days.

59
00:03:45,867 --> 00:03:47,433
Did you say decent?

60
00:03:47,567 --> 00:03:50,033
Is this the same as a police
officer like me

61
00:03:50,167 --> 00:03:51,900
helping you find your friend?

62
00:03:52,033 --> 00:03:52,800
That's right.

63
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:54,467
I hope so,

64
00:03:54,633 --> 00:03:57,633
but I'm the only one asking
questions among the three of us.

65
00:03:57,767 --> 00:04:01,033
Your questions aren't
for Cherry, but for me.

66
00:04:01,167 --> 00:04:06,300
Hey, no, but what are you
looking for in a man?

67
00:04:07,633 --> 00:04:12,233
Are we going to find my friend
Cherry or my future boyfriend?

68
00:04:12,367 --> 00:04:14,000
We can do both.

69
00:04:14,133 --> 00:04:16,567
You're such a flirt, Sir.

70
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:17,900
Okay, why don't we do this
instead?

71
00:04:18,033 --> 00:04:22,067
If you find Cherry,
I'll agree to date you.

72
00:04:23,333 --> 00:04:24,400
Wait a minute...

73
00:04:24,533 --> 00:04:27,867
Just because we're asking
about you,

74
00:04:28,033 --> 00:04:29,633
it doesn't mean we want
to date you right away.

75
00:04:29,767 --> 00:04:30,633
You don't want it?

76
00:04:30,767 --> 00:04:31,500
Joke!

77
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:34,433
- Come on, let's go find Cherry.
- Come on.

78
00:04:38,633 --> 00:04:40,200
Sir?

79
00:04:40,333 --> 00:04:41,900
Okay, Sir.

80
00:04:42,033 --> 00:04:42,967
What did Sir say?

81
00:04:44,567 --> 00:04:45,767
We'll regroup.

82
00:04:45,900 --> 00:04:46,800
- Come on.
- Let's go.

83
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:52,400
But, Peach, what exactly are you
looking for in a guy?

84
00:04:54,933 --> 00:04:56,967
Our search was also negative,
Sir.

85
00:04:57,100 --> 00:04:58,267
Negative?

86
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,567
It's Peach you're interrogating.

87
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:04,033
Sir, I'm not a part of that.

88
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,933
Wait, Sir. Could it be
that she's also a victim

89
00:05:06,067 --> 00:05:08,633
of the human trafficking case
our station is handling?

90
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:09,633
Trafficking?

91
00:05:10,667 --> 00:05:12,833
Is that when people
are taken abroad?

92
00:05:12,967 --> 00:05:15,500
Yes, and then sold to whoever.

93
00:05:17,633 --> 00:05:19,067
Don't worry, girls.

94
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,500
We'll find Cherry.

95
00:05:20,633 --> 00:05:23,400
You two are really scaring Apple
and Peach.

96
00:05:23,533 --> 00:05:25,533
But is that true, Sir Fred?

97
00:05:27,367 --> 00:05:29,600
It's true that there is a human
trafficking syndicate now,

98
00:05:29,733 --> 00:05:31,100
but don't worry.

99
00:05:31,233 --> 00:05:34,333
We won't stop
until we find Cherry.

100
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:38,100
Besides, there are many possible
reasons why she stood you up.

101
00:05:38,233 --> 00:05:41,300
For example,
does she have a boyfriend?

102
00:05:41,433 --> 00:05:42,567
Cherry?

103
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:43,433
No!

104
00:05:43,567 --> 00:05:44,600
<i> Balut!</i>

105
00:05:44,733 --> 00:05:46,133
<i> Penoy, balut!</i>

106
00:05:46,267 --> 00:05:48,000
Boss!

107
00:05:48,133 --> 00:05:51,800
Wait, did you come by here last
night? Around six o'clock?

108
00:05:51,933 --> 00:05:52,900
Yes, Sir.

109
00:05:53,033 --> 00:05:54,900
There are a lot of people
waiting here for a ride

110
00:05:55,033 --> 00:05:55,733
every night.

111
00:05:55,867 --> 00:05:56,667
Why?

112
00:05:56,800 --> 00:06:00,000
Mister, have you seen
this woman?

113
00:06:00,133 --> 00:06:01,900
Yes, I saw her.

114
00:06:02,033 --> 00:06:04,600
Wait, did something bad happen
to her?

115
00:06:04,733 --> 00:06:06,033
Why did you say that?

116
00:06:06,167 --> 00:06:07,900
Because I saw her last night,

117
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:10,900
she was dragged by a man
in a car.

118
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:21,933
Garcia, let's separate.
Go there.

119
00:06:22,067 --> 00:06:22,833
Okay.

120
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:30,533
Enriquez, go there.
I'll take this side.

121
00:06:30,667 --> 00:06:31,567
Yes, Sir.

122
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:10,667
What's the update, Sir?

123
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:13,300
We should be thankful we got
a lead from the<i> balut</i> vendor.

124
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:15,200
We saw a CCTV footage.

125
00:07:15,367 --> 00:07:18,200
Cherry was picked up
and taken away by a vehicle

126
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:21,033
with a plate number, AAO 7762.

127
00:07:21,167 --> 00:07:23,667
We backtracked it, so we know
where she is now.

128
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:24,733
Let's go.

129
00:07:24,867 --> 00:07:25,833
Apple.

130
00:08:17,667 --> 00:08:18,600
Positive.

131
00:08:18,733 --> 00:08:20,367
This is the license plate
that took Cherry.

132
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,067
I'm sure she's inside.

133
00:08:38,733 --> 00:08:40,033
Who are you?

134
00:08:40,167 --> 00:08:44,233
I've been following you,
watching you,

135
00:08:44,367 --> 00:08:45,833
and fantasizing about you
for a long time now,

136
00:08:45,967 --> 00:08:49,000
but you're not paying attention
to me!

137
00:08:49,133 --> 00:08:50,633
Why?

138
00:08:50,767 --> 00:08:51,967
Is it because I'm ugly?

139
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:55,133
I'm begging you, let me go!

140
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:57,000
There's nothing you can do.

141
00:08:57,133 --> 00:08:58,367
You're mine now.

142
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:04,867
Don't, don't, please! Don't!

143
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,100
Don't struggle anymore.

144
00:09:07,233 --> 00:09:09,667
Didn't you want this too?

145
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:11,667
Don't!

146
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:14,100
Don't...

147
00:09:14,233 --> 00:09:15,733
You're going to like this.

148
00:09:15,867 --> 00:09:17,933
Help!

149
00:09:18,067 --> 00:09:20,267
- That's what I want.
- Help!

150
00:09:21,167 --> 00:09:22,333
You two, stay here.

151
00:09:22,467 --> 00:09:23,833
No matter what happens,
just stay here.

152
00:09:23,967 --> 00:09:24,667
Let's go.

153
00:09:32,700 --> 00:09:34,600
- Help!
- Don't fight anymore!

154
00:09:34,733 --> 00:09:36,333
You'll be mine!

155
00:09:36,467 --> 00:09:37,900
No!

156
00:09:38,033 --> 00:09:39,267
Didn't you want this too?

157
00:09:40,567 --> 00:09:42,167
Help!

158
00:10:06,967 --> 00:10:09,267
<i> Help!</i>

159
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,467
<i> Help!</i>

160
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,333
Hey!

161
00:10:12,467 --> 00:10:14,800
- Who are you?
- You're a maniac!

162
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:15,867
Come here!

163
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,700
You're a maniac!

164
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:20,933
- Please don't hurt him!
- You're safe.

165
00:10:22,133 --> 00:10:24,167
- Don't!
- Come here!

166
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:26,133
Don't!

167
00:10:26,267 --> 00:10:27,500
Stop!

168
00:10:27,633 --> 00:10:29,233
Enough!

169
00:10:29,367 --> 00:10:30,767
Cherry, what are you doing?

170
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:33,567
We're saving you.
Isn't he abusing you?

171
00:10:34,867 --> 00:10:36,833
You don't understand.

172
00:10:36,967 --> 00:10:39,600
He's my boyfriend.

173
00:10:39,733 --> 00:10:41,400
He's your boyfriend?

174
00:10:41,533 --> 00:10:43,333
Babe, are you okay?

175
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:46,433
It hurts here.

176
00:10:46,567 --> 00:10:47,600
Oh no...

177
00:10:47,733 --> 00:10:49,000
It hurts here, too.

178
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,333
Are you okay?

179
00:10:52,467 --> 00:10:54,033
Sorry, Babe!

180
00:10:54,267 --> 00:10:55,700
Sorry!

181
00:10:59,667 --> 00:11:02,633
The handsome enemy went there!

182
00:11:02,767 --> 00:11:03,533
Wait.

183
00:11:03,667 --> 00:11:05,300
I'm the only handsome enemy.

184
00:11:23,267 --> 00:11:24,333
You too!

185
00:11:31,467 --> 00:11:32,500
What?

186
00:11:33,433 --> 00:11:34,367
What?

187
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:37,500
What is this?

188
00:11:59,633 --> 00:12:01,867
Nothing! More!

189
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,633
That was only my left hand!

190
00:12:06,233 --> 00:12:08,233
You can't hurt me!

191
00:12:08,367 --> 00:12:09,967
Really?

192
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:11,767
No left, no right!

193
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:13,033
You can't hurt me!

194
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:17,033
Even foreigners are hurt
by that!

195
00:12:20,133 --> 00:12:21,167
What?

196
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:23,733
What?

197
00:13:10,067 --> 00:13:13,667
Where are the girls?

198
00:13:15,033 --> 00:13:17,833
Where did they go?

199
00:13:17,967 --> 00:13:18,767
They're...

200
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:21,400
they're taking them
to Switzerland.

201
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:39,867
- Cherry.
- Cherry.

202
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,267
Cherry...

203
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:43,767
- What happened to you, Cherry?
- Are you okay?

204
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:46,000
Sorry, sorry, I just want to ask
for one last time...

205
00:13:46,133 --> 00:13:47,500
but...

206
00:13:47,633 --> 00:13:49,500
is this really your boyfriend?

207
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:52,733
Yes, Sir. Why?

208
00:13:52,867 --> 00:13:53,967
Why, Sir?

209
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:55,833
Don't we look good together?

210
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,500
Maybe he's gifted.

211
00:13:57,633 --> 00:13:59,000
Maybe.

212
00:13:59,133 --> 00:14:01,200
He's not.

213
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:04,000
Babe, don't embarrass me
in front of them.

214
00:14:04,133 --> 00:14:06,233
You shouldn't be embarrassed.

215
00:14:07,867 --> 00:14:09,467
I think I know already.

216
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:13,000
You're kind.
You have a golden heart.

217
00:14:13,133 --> 00:14:15,133
Oh no, not either.

218
00:14:15,267 --> 00:14:17,267
He always makes me cry.

219
00:14:17,733 --> 00:14:18,833
Why?

220
00:14:18,967 --> 00:14:21,133
In that state,
are you still a womanizer?

221
00:14:21,267 --> 00:14:22,167
Not really.

222
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:24,767
The thing is,
Cherry is suffocating me.

223
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:26,533
She wants us to video call
all the time.

224
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:27,800
What about my phone load, right?

225
00:14:29,033 --> 00:14:30,367
You know...

226
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:32,400
what you did was no joke.

227
00:14:32,533 --> 00:14:35,667
You took the police officers'
time and attention,

228
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:38,833
instead of giving it to those
who are really in need.

229
00:14:38,967 --> 00:14:42,000
Your friends kept calling you,
but you didn't answer.

230
00:14:42,133 --> 00:14:46,533
Besides, it's not appropriate
to roleplay rape and abduction.

231
00:14:46,667 --> 00:14:47,967
Sorry, Sir.

232
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,667
I just really miss my boyfriend.

233
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:57,267
So when I saw him, I forgot
about Apple and Peach.

234
00:14:58,867 --> 00:15:01,967
That's what Cherry said.
She wants me to kidnap her.

235
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:09,000
Sir, we have to go
to Switzerland.

236
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:11,300
Switzerland? You can't.

237
00:15:11,433 --> 00:15:15,500
Your remaining budget is just
enough to bring Selena home.

238
00:15:16,933 --> 00:15:20,200
And besides, we can't approve
an additional budget for that.

239
00:15:24,367 --> 00:15:26,433
Good day!

240
00:15:26,567 --> 00:15:28,067
Sir, don't worry.

241
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:33,033
We can use my credit card
because my credit limit is high.

242
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:34,433
If you want,
you can come with us.

243
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,100
You don't understand.

244
00:15:37,233 --> 00:15:41,633
This isn't about whether
you have a budget or not.

245
00:15:41,767 --> 00:15:45,733
Maybe you're forgetting
what our priority is...

246
00:15:45,867 --> 00:15:48,133
getting Selena back here
in the Philippines.

247
00:15:51,467 --> 00:15:53,333
Sir, what about my godsister?

248
00:15:53,467 --> 00:15:55,400
Let's worry about her
next time.

249
00:15:55,533 --> 00:15:59,533
What's important is to get
Selena back here,

250
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:01,167
and that's an order!

251
00:16:01,733 --> 00:16:02,733
But, Sir...

252
00:16:20,367 --> 00:16:21,900
Cherry, didn't I tell you

253
00:16:22,033 --> 00:16:23,233
that we should just end
this relationship?

254
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:24,433
I don't want this anymore,
Cherry.

255
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:27,033
I don't want what we are doing
for a long time now!

256
00:16:27,167 --> 00:16:29,333
What are you saying, Jo?

257
00:16:29,467 --> 00:16:31,267
You want to end
this relationship?

258
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:32,600
Are you tired?

259
00:16:32,733 --> 00:16:33,800
Yes!

260
00:16:33,933 --> 00:16:39,533
I am so, so, so, so, so, so,
so, so, so tired of you!

261
00:16:39,667 --> 00:16:41,267
Babe, wait a minute!
Don't leave me!

262
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:43,667
Come on, Peach.
Come on, help me.

263
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:53,667
This is the biggest mystery
that happened in Calabari.

264
00:17:05,733 --> 00:17:07,133
Stupid.

265
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,133
Hello, Markus?

266
00:17:11,867 --> 00:17:15,667
Roman, these three
are a big problem here.

267
00:17:15,833 --> 00:17:16,767
Sorry.

268
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:19,133
I'm not there.
I can't control the situation.

269
00:17:19,267 --> 00:17:21,567
They have Selena.

270
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:23,500
Roman, we'll get in trouble
with the boss

271
00:17:23,633 --> 00:17:25,700
when that girl gets back
to the Philippines.

272
00:17:26,733 --> 00:17:27,500
Okay.

273
00:17:27,633 --> 00:17:28,867
What are you planning?

274
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,633
See you later at four o'clock.

275
00:17:37,767 --> 00:17:39,033
- Mar!
- Captain!

276
00:17:39,167 --> 00:17:40,833
- That's enough.
- Captain!

277
00:17:40,967 --> 00:17:43,167
Four o'clock at the village
office, okay?

278
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:44,767
Captain, let's eat breakfast.

279
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:45,800
What breakfast?

280
00:17:45,933 --> 00:17:46,967
- You've eaten already.
- I haven't eaten.

281
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:49,167
You're just feeding us porridge.

282
00:17:49,333 --> 00:17:51,233
Let's go to the village office,
let's go straight there.

283
00:17:53,533 --> 00:17:55,167
What is that?

284
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:56,700
Where are you taking her?

285
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:57,767
Abdul!

286
00:17:57,900 --> 00:18:00,133
- Mar!
- Captain!

287
00:18:00,267 --> 00:18:03,367
- Let's chase them!
- Captain!

288
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:04,900
Hey! What happened?

289
00:18:05,033 --> 00:18:06,167
They kidnapped the captain!

290
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:06,900
What?

291
00:18:07,033 --> 00:18:08,633
- Where?
- There!

292
00:18:08,767 --> 00:18:09,767
Call for help!

293
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:13,400
- Boss, help! Help!
- Councilor!

294
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:15,200
- They kidnapped the captain!
- What happened?

295
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:17,633
- The red van!
- All right, get on board.

296
00:18:17,767 --> 00:18:18,833
Come on!

297
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:23,233
Hello, Major.

298
00:18:31,967 --> 00:18:33,467
There, let's stop here.

299
00:18:40,933 --> 00:18:42,700
Maybe it's just here.

300
00:18:42,833 --> 00:18:44,133
Where did it go?

301
00:18:44,267 --> 00:18:45,767
What will happen
to Grandmother Isang?

302
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:47,100
Dude, isn't that it?

303
00:18:47,233 --> 00:18:48,733
That red one? No, here.

304
00:18:48,867 --> 00:18:51,433
Maybe something bad might happen
to her.

305
00:18:51,567 --> 00:18:52,767
Hello, I need your help.

306
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:54,133
We're looking for a van.

307
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:55,467
Do you remember
the plate number?

308
00:18:55,633 --> 00:18:56,367
Yes.

309
00:18:57,633 --> 00:18:59,933
ANQ 1013.

310
00:19:00,067 --> 00:19:01,267
- Red van!
- Red van!

311
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:04,967
We're looking for the red van
with a plate number, ANQ 1013.

312
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:07,033
Okay, let me know.
It's an emergency.

313
00:19:07,167 --> 00:19:07,967
Thank you.

314
00:19:09,767 --> 00:19:11,000
What?

315
00:19:11,133 --> 00:19:12,567
Okay, let's go.

316
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:14,367
Let's get in the car first.
Maybe we can find it.

317
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:15,667
Let's go! Hurry.

318
00:20:00,467 --> 00:20:02,667
Enriquez, have some coffee
first.

319
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:05,667
Thank you, Sir.

320
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:12,633
I understand the chief, Sir,

321
00:20:12,767 --> 00:20:16,133
but it's hard to hear
that Reign is not a priority.

322
00:20:23,733 --> 00:20:24,767
Enriquez...

323
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:31,433
this kind of operation
is not that simple.

324
00:20:31,567 --> 00:20:35,033
What will the chief do
if I separate from you?

325
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:38,367
Separate from us?
What do you mean?

326
00:20:40,167 --> 00:20:41,733
I'll stay here.

327
00:20:41,867 --> 00:20:43,167
I'll find Reign.

328
00:20:45,067 --> 00:20:46,600
That's insubordination.

329
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:50,033
That's the mildest case
they can come up with.

330
00:20:50,167 --> 00:20:52,267
And the ones most hated
by those at the top

331
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,433
are people like that,
the stubborn ones.

332
00:20:54,567 --> 00:20:56,367
That could ruin your career.

333
00:21:11,767 --> 00:21:13,900
Sir, I can't believe
that I'm saying this.

334
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:18,300
But I'm going to find Reign,

335
00:21:18,433 --> 00:21:20,433
even if it ruins my career.

336
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,800
Put me down!

337
00:21:37,933 --> 00:21:39,433
What did I do wrong?

338
00:21:39,567 --> 00:21:40,733
What did I do?

339
00:21:40,867 --> 00:21:42,433
Grandmother!

340
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:45,067
I didn't do anything wrong
to you!

341
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:48,400
- Why are you doing this to me?
- Sir, it's my grandmother!

342
00:21:48,533 --> 00:21:49,800
Stop asking so many questions!

343
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:52,500
Do you want me to pull
the trigger?

344
00:21:58,367 --> 00:21:59,733
You animal!

345
00:21:59,867 --> 00:22:02,033
What are you doing
to my grandmother?

346
00:22:02,167 --> 00:22:04,900
I know you have Selena Madrigal.

347
00:22:05,033 --> 00:22:07,100
Give her back to me,

348
00:22:07,233 --> 00:22:09,800
or I'll blow your grandmother's
head off.

349
00:22:09,933 --> 00:22:11,733
Don't hurt my grandmother!

350
00:22:11,867 --> 00:22:16,033
If you want, just take me
instead of my grandmother!

351
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:17,800
You're really stubborn.

352
00:22:19,067 --> 00:22:22,200
Perfect, the cathedral here
in Milan is beautiful.

353
00:22:22,333 --> 00:22:24,433
Just pray for your grandmother.

354
00:22:55,267 --> 00:22:56,200
Enriquez,

355
00:22:56,433 --> 00:22:57,700
how are we going to find
what we're looking for here?

356
00:22:57,833 --> 00:23:00,167
Switzerland is so big!

357
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:02,300
I know my credit limit is high,

358
00:23:02,433 --> 00:23:04,067
but could you please
not abuse it?

359
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:05,767
You just want to go
for a stroll.

360
00:23:05,900 --> 00:23:07,900
Bok, secure Selena.

361
00:23:08,033 --> 00:23:09,267
What do you mean by secure?

362
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:11,433
You will lock me up in a hotel
or in a safehouse?

363
00:23:11,567 --> 00:23:12,733
That's why I came with you,

364
00:23:12,867 --> 00:23:15,167
because I want to get revenge
on the demon who kidnapped me!

365
00:23:15,300 --> 00:23:17,167
Have you heard anything
about Selena?

366
00:23:17,300 --> 00:23:19,600
We still haven't heard
from our man at Station 12.

367
00:23:19,733 --> 00:23:22,233
The police officers who followed
you to Milan and Dubai

368
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,533
still haven't come home.

369
00:23:23,667 --> 00:23:25,167
So be careful there
in Switzerland

370
00:23:25,300 --> 00:23:27,333
because they might
still be after you.

371
00:23:27,467 --> 00:23:28,333
That's Markus!

372
00:23:32,233 --> 00:23:33,000
Watch.

373
00:23:33,133 --> 00:23:36,300
You won't hit me even once.
